body:
This is in 1.6.0-beta.4:

`Mar 20 04:46:39 ip-172-20-45-81 kubelet[1552]: W0320 04:46:39.953264    1552 helpers.go:158] Unknown protocol "TCP": defaulting to TCP`

Some context:

```
Mar 20 04:46:39 ip-172-20-45-81 kubelet[1552]: I0320 04:46:39.947856    1552 kuberuntime_manager.go:458] Container {Name:etcd-container Image:gcr.io/google_containers/etcd:2.2.1 Command:[/bin/sh -c if [ -e /usr/local/bin/migrate-if-needed.sh ]; then /usr/local/bin/migrate-if-needed.sh 1>>/var/log/etcd.log 2>&1; fi; /usr/local/bin/etcd 1>>/var/log/etcd.log 2>&1] Args:[] WorkingDir: Ports:[{Name:serverport HostPort:2380 ContainerPort:2380 Protocol:TCP HostIP:} {Name:clientport HostPort:4001 ContainerPort:4001 Protocol:TCP HostIP:}] EnvFrom:[] Env:[{Name:DATA_DIRECTORY Value:/var/etcd/data ValueFrom:nil} {Name:ETCD_ADVERTISE_CLIENT_URLS Value:http://etcd-b.internal.mar19c.awsdata.com:4001 ValueFrom:nil} {Name:ETCD_DATA_DIR Value:/var/etcd/data ValueFrom:nil} {Name:ETCD_INITIAL_ADVERTISE_PEER_URLS Value:http://etcd-b.internal.mar19c.awsdata.com:2380 ValueFrom:nil} {Name:ETCD_INITIAL_CLUSTER Value:etcd-b=http://etcd-b.internal.mar19c.awsdata.com:2380 ValueFrom:nil} {Name:ETCD_INITIAL_CLUSTER_STATE Value:new ValueFrom:nil} {Name:ETCD_INITIAL_CLUSTER_TOKEN Value:etcd-cluster-token-etcd ValueFrom:nil} {Name:ETCD_LISTEN_CLIENT_URLS Value:http://0.0.0.0:4001 ValueFrom:nil} {Name:ETCD_LISTEN_PEER_URLS Value:http://0.0.0.0:2380 ValueFrom:nil} {Name:ETCD_NAME Value:etcd-b ValueFrom:nil} {Name:TARGET_STORAGE Value:etcd2 ValueFrom:nil} {Name:TARGET_VERSION Value:2.2.1 ValueFrom:nil}] Resources:{Limits:map[] Requests:map[cpu:{i:{value:200 scale:-3} d:{Dec:<nil>} s:200m Format:DecimalSI}]} VolumeMounts:[{Name:varetcdata ReadOnly:false MountPath:/var/etcd/ SubPath:} {Name:varlogetcd ReadOnly:false MountPath:/var/log/etcd.log SubPath:}] LivenessProbe:&Probe{Handler:Handler{Exec:nil,HTTPGet:&HTTPGetAction{Path:/health,Port:4001,Host:127.0.0.1,Scheme:HTTP,HTTPHeaders:[],},TCPSocket:nil,},InitialDelaySeconds:15,TimeoutSeconds:15,PeriodSeconds:10,SuccessThreshold:1,FailureThreshold:3,} ReadinessProbe:nil Lifecycle:nil TerminationMessagePath:/dev/termination-log TerminationMessagePolicy:File ImagePullPolicy:IfNotPresent SecurityContext:nil Stdin:false StdinOnce:false TTY:false} is d
Mar 20 04:46:39 ip-172-20-45-81 kubelet[1552]: ead, but RestartPolicy says that we should restart it.
Mar 20 04:46:39 ip-172-20-45-81 kubelet[1552]: W0320 04:46:39.953264    1552 helpers.go:158] Unknown protocol "TCP": defaulting to TCP
Mar 20 04:46:39 ip-172-20-45-81 kubelet[1552]: W0320 04:46:39.953280    1552 helpers.go:158] Unknown protocol "TCP": defaulting to TCP
```

The line number suggests it is here: https://github.com/kubernetes/kubernetes/blob/master/pkg/kubelet/dockershim/helpers.go#L158 

I _think_ this is because dockershim now uses a protobuf object `runtimeapi.PortMapping` and Protocol is now an int.  And `string(1)` is allowed in go (apparently) - `string(65)` is "A".

And the comedic error is because Protocol implements `String()`

If this is the error, there's something fishy going on because all our UDP tests should fail?
